-- Lloyds Said to Offer 825 Million Pounds of Loan-Backed Bonds
-- B y   E s t e b a n   D u a r t e
-- 2012-03-16T10:00:33Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-16/lloyds-said-to-offer-825-million-pounds-of-loan-backed-bonds.html
Lloyds Banking Group Plc (LLOY)  is selling
825 million pounds of top-rated bonds backed by loans to small
and medium-sized companies, according to a person with knowledge
of the transaction.  The securities with a weighted average life of 4.4 years
will be issued by Sandown Gold 2012-1, the person said. The
issue includes lower-rated notes that will be retained.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Esteban Duarte in Madrid at 
 eduarterubia@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
